name: Planned Systems International
overview: Planned Systems International, Inc. provides information technology (IT) solutions and services to federal government and private sector organizations. The company offers its products and services in fields of full systems lifecycle support, distributed learning support, healthcare IT solutions, information assurance, enterprise-wide solutions and authentication, management improvement services, enterprise infrastructure support, e-business and Web/e-Commerce, and green enterprise solutions, as well as in the fields of systems development, advisory and assistance services, information security, network/desktop services, and distance learning. It serves defense, awards and accolades, and federal civilian clients in the United States. The company was founded in 1988 and is based in Columbia, Maryland with additional offices and corporate facilities in Columbia, Maryland; San Antonio, Texas; and St Petersburg, Florida. It also has offices in Arlington and Falls Church, Virginia, as well as corporate facilities in Warrenton, Virginia; Washington, the District of Columbia; Shanghai, China; and Barcelona, Spain.
